	<h1>When a Man Loves</h1>
</header>

	<section id="film-detail-container">
		<img src="../static/images/m12.jpeg" alt="Film poster">

		<p><em>When a Man Loves</em> is a silent historical drama film directed by Alan Crosland, starring John Barrymore and Dolores Costello.</p>

		<p>Warner Bros. Pictures produced the film.</p>

		<p>
			It was released by Warner Bros. Pictures on February 3, 1927, with a runtime of 111 minutes.

			
				It had a budget of $528,000  and made $1 million at the box office.
				When adjusted for inflation in 2023, that's approximately equivalent to $9.1 million and $17.9 million, respectively.
			
		</p>

		<p>
			The film was written by Bess Meredyth, with Henry Hadley composing the filmâ€™s music. Byron Haskin oversaw cinematography, and Harold McCord helped with editing the film.
		</p>

		<p><a href="https://archive.org/details/when-a-man-loves_1927">View an archived version of <em>When a Man Loves</em>.</a></p>

		<p><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/When_a_Man_Loves">View the Wikipedia entry for <em>When a Man Loves</em>.</a></p>

		<p><a href="../index.html">Return to the list</a> to select a different film.</p>
